SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ENDOWMENTS PROVIDE A LONG-TERM STREAM OF INCOME FOR MEETING UNIVERSITY NEEDS. ENDOWMENTS MAY BE DESIGNATED FOR SCHOLARSHIPS, ACADEMIC PROGRAM SUPPORT, GRADUATE FELLOWSHIPS, ENDOWED CHAIRS OR OTHER SPECIFIC AREAS.
THE FOUNDATION AND THE ASSOCIATION ARE EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE.

QUARTERLY DISBURSEMENTS OF SCHOLARSHIPS ARE REPORTED AND REVIEWED FOR ACCURACY BY CWU FOUNDATION STAFF AND THE CWU SCHOLARSHIP OFFICE REPORTS CONSIST OF STUDENT ID NUMBERS, NAME OF THE SCHOLARSHIP, AMOUNT OFFERED AND AMOUNT DISBURSED SO THAT THIS CAN BE TRACED TO THE STUDENT FINANCIAL REPORT TO SHOW THE STUDENT RECEIVING THIS AWARD. MONITORING BY THE SYSTEM AND INDIVIDUALS HELP INSURE THAT THE CRITERIA OF THE SCHOLARSHIP GIVEN IS BEING HONORED.

THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR IS AN EMPLOYEE OF CENTRAL WASHINGTON UNIVERSITY. THE UNIVERSITY BASES THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S SALARY ON A MARKET-BASED SALARY SURVEY. THE FOUNDATION DOES NOT PAY THE WAGES. THE AMOUNT OF COMPENSATION REPORTED ON PART VII OF FORM 990 IS THE FOUNDATION'S ALLOCABLE SHARE OF THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S COMPENSATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE 990 IS REVIEWED BY MANAGEMENT AND THE FINANCE AND AUDIT COMMITTEE BEFORE FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CONFLICT OF INTEREST GENERAL POLICY STATEMENTS ARE GIVEN TO THE BOARD MEMBERS ANNUALLY. THE STATEMENT REVIEWS OUR POLICY THAT FOR BUSINESS TRANSACTIONS INVOLVING THE FOUNDATION AND THE PERSONAL OR BUSINESS AFFAIRS OF A DIRECTOR, OFFICER, OR STAFF MEMBER WILL BE APPROVED IN ADVANCE BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. FURTHER INFORMATION ABOUT SPECIFIC APPLICATION OF FINANCIAL INTERESTS AND RELATIONSHIPS, SPECIAL PRIVILEGES, FAVORS AND USE OF UNIVERSITY PROPERTY IS CONTAINED IN THE POLICY FOR REVIEW. EACH BOARD MEMBER REVIEWS THE POLICY, FILLS OUT THE QUESTIONNAIRE AND SIGNS THAT THEY AGREE TO INFORM THE BOARD CHAIR, EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND FELLOW DIRECTORS OF ANY CONFLICT THAT MAY BE DEVELOPING AND IN ALL SUCH CASES THEY WILL ABSTAIN FROM DISCUSSION AND VOTING, AND THEIR DISCLOSURE AND ABSTENTION WILL BE A MATTER OF RECORD. THE SIGNED FORM IS RETAINED IN THE CWU FOUNDATION RECORDS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR IS AN EMPLOYEE OF CENTRAL WASHINGTON UNIVERSITY. THE UNIVERSITY BASES THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S SALARY ON A MARKET-BASED SALARY SURVEY. THE FOUNDATION DOES NOT PAY THE WAGES, IT PREPARERS AN ALLOCATION TO RECORD THE PERSONNEL CONTRIBUTION FROM CWU TO THE FOUNDATION.
